{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["29-JOL-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"JOL"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Joel \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The Book of Joel \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Joel \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Jol \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt2","content":["The Book of \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Joel \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"JOL 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JOL 1:1"},"The LORD’s",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, “LORD” or “ALLAH” is the translation of Allah’s Proper\nName."]}],"caller":"+"}," word that came to Joel, the son of Pethuel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JOL 1:2"},"Hear this, you elders, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["And listen, all you inhabitants of the land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Has this ever happened in your days, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or in the days of your fathers? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JOL 1:3"},"Tell your children about it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have your children tell their children, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their children, another generation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JOL 1:4"},"What the swarming locust has left, the great locust has eaten.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["What the great locust has left, the grasshopper has eaten. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["What the grasshopper has left, the caterpillar has eaten. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JOL 1:5"},"Wake up, you drunkards, and weep! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Wail, all you drinkers of wine, because of the sweet wine; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for it is cut off from your mouth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JOL 1:6"},"For a nation has come up on my land, strong, and without number.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His teeth are the teeth of a lion, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he has the fangs of a lioness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JOL 1:7"},"He has laid my vine waste, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and stripped my fig tree. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has stripped its bark, and thrown it away. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Its branches are made white. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JOL 1:8"},"Mourn like a virgin dressed in sackcloth for the husband of her youth!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JOL 1:9"},"The meal offering and the drink offering are cut off from the LORD’s house.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The priests, the LORD’s ministers, mourn. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JOL 1:10"},"The field is laid waste. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The land mourns, for the grain is destroyed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The new wine has dried up, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the oil languishes. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JOL 1:11"},"Be confounded, you farmers! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Wail, you vineyard keepers; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the wheat and for the barley; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the harvest of the field has perished. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JOL 1:12"},"The vine has dried up, and the fig tree withered; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the pomegranate tree, the palm tree also, and the apple tree,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even all of the trees of the field are withered; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for joy has withered away from the sons of men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JOL 1:13"},"Put on sackcloth and mourn, you priests! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Wail, you ministers of the altar. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Come, lie all night in sackcloth, you ministers of my Allah,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew word rendered “Allah” is “אֱלֹהִ֑ים” (Elohim)."]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the meal offering and the drink offering are withheld from your Allah’s house.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JOL 1:14"},"Sanctify a fast. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Call a solemn assembly. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Gather the elders, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all the inhabitants of the land, to the house of the LORD, your Allah,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and cry to the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JOL 1:15"},"Alas for the day! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For the day of the LORD is at hand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and it will come as destruction from the Almighty. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JOL 1:16"},"Isn’t the food cut off before our eyes; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["joy and gladness from the house of our Allah? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JOL 1:17"},"The seeds rot under their clods. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The granaries are laid desolate. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The barns are broken down, for the grain has withered. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JOL 1:18"},"How the animals groan! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The herds of livestock are perplexed, because they have no pasture.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yes, the flocks of sheep are made desolate. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JOL 1:19"},"The LORD, I cry to you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For the fire has devoured the pastures of the wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the flame has burnt all the trees of the field. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JOL 1:20"},"Yes, the animals of the field pant to you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the water brooks have dried up, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["And the fire has devoured the pastures of the wilderness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"JOL 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JOL 2:1"},"Blow the trumpet in Zion, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and sound an alarm in my holy mountain! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let all the inhabitants of the land tremble, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the day of the LORD comes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for it is close at hand: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JOL 2:2"},"A day of darkness and gloominess, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a day of clouds and thick darkness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["As the dawn spreading on the mountains, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a great and strong people; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["there has never been the like, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["neither will there be any more after them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even to the years of many generations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JOL 2:3"},"A fire devours before them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and behind them, a flame burns. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The land is as the garden of Eden before them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and behind them, a desolate wilderness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yes, and no one has escaped them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JOL 2:4"},"Their appearance is as the appearance of horses, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they run as horsemen. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JOL 2:5"},"Like the noise of chariots on the tops of the mountains, they leap,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like the noise of a flame of fire that devours the stubble, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a strong people set in battle array. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JOL 2:6"},"At their presence the peoples are in anguish. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All faces have grown pale. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JOL 2:7"},"They run like mighty men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They climb the wall like warriors. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They each march in his line, and they don’t swerve off course.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JOL 2:8"},"Neither does one jostle another; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they march everyone in his path, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they burst through the defences, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and don’t break ranks. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JOL 2:9"},"They rush on the city. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They run on the wall. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They climb up into the houses. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They enter in at the windows like thieves. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JOL 2:10"},"The earth quakes before them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The heavens tremble. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The sun and the moon are darkened, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the stars withdraw their shining. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JOL 2:11"},"The LORD thunders his voice before his army; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for his forces are very great; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he is strong who obeys his command; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the day of the LORD is great and very awesome, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and who can endure it? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JOL 2:12"},"“Yet even now,” says the LORD, “turn to me with all your heart,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and with fasting, and with weeping, and with mourning.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JOL 2:13"},"Tear your heart, and not your garments, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and turn to the LORD, your Allah; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he is gracious and merciful, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["slow to anger, and abundant in loving kindness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and relents from sending calamity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JOL 2:14"},"Who knows? He may turn and relent, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and leave a blessing behind him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even a meal offering and a drink offering to the LORD, your Allah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JOL 2:15"},"Blow the trumpet in Zion! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Sanctify a fast. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Call a solemn assembly. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JOL 2:16"},"Gather the people. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Sanctify the assembly. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Assemble the elders. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Gather the children, and those who nurse from breasts. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let the bridegroom go out of his room, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the bride out of her room. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JOL 2:17"},"Let the priests, the ministers of the LORD, weep between the porch and the altar,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let them say, “Spare your people, LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and don’t give your heritage to reproach, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that the nations should rule over them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why should they say amongst the peoples, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Where is their Allah?’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JOL 2:18"},"Then the LORD was jealous for his land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["And had pity on his people. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JOL 2:19"},"The LORD answered his people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “הִנֵּה”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used\nas an interjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," I will send you grain, new wine, and oil,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you will be satisfied with them; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will no more make you a reproach amongst the nations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JOL 2:20"},"But I will remove the northern army far away from you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will drive it into a barren and desolate land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["its front into the eastern sea, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its back into the western sea; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its stench will come up, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its bad smell will rise.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Surely he has done great things. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JOL 2:21"},"Land, don’t be afraid. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Be glad and rejoice, for the LORD has done great things. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JOL 2:22"},"Don’t be afraid, you animals of the field; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the pastures of the wilderness spring up, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the tree bears its fruit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The fig tree and the vine yield their strength. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JOL 2:23"},"“Be glad then, you children of Zion, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and rejoice in the LORD, your Allah; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he gives you the early rain in just measure, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he causes the rain to come down for you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the early rain and the latter rain, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as before. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JOL 2:24"},"The threshing floors will be full of wheat, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the vats will overflow with new wine and oil. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JOL 2:25"},"I will restore to you the years that the swarming locust has eaten,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the great locust, the grasshopper, and the caterpillar, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["my great army, which I sent amongst you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JOL 2:26"},"You will have plenty to eat, and be satisfied, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will praise the name of the LORD, your Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who has dealt wondrously with you; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and my people will never again be disappointed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JOL 2:27"},"You will know that I am amongst Israel, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and that I am the LORD, your Allah, and there is no one else;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and my people will never again be disappointed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JOL 2:28"},"“It will happen afterward, that I will pour out my Spirit on all flesh;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your sons and your daughters will prophesy. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your old men will dream dreams. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your young men will see visions. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JOL 2:29"},"And also on the servants and on the handmaids in those days,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will pour out my Spirit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JOL 2:30"},"I will show wonders in the heavens and in the earth: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["blood, fire, and pillars of smoke. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JOL 2:31"},"The sun will be turned into darkness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the moon into blood, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["before the great and terrible day of the LORD comes. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JOL 2:32"},"It will happen that whoever will call on the LORD’s name shall be saved;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for in Mount Zion and in Jerusalem there will be those who escape,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as the LORD has said, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and amongst the remnant, those whom the LORD calls. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"JOL 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JOL 3:1"},"“For, behold, in those days, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and in that time, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I restore the fortunes of Judah and Jerusalem, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JOL 3:2"},"I will gather all nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will bring them down into the valley of Jehoshaphat; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will execute judgement on them there for my people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and for my heritage, Israel, whom they have scattered amongst the nations.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have divided my land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JOL 3:3"},"and have cast lots for my people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have given a boy for a prostitute, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and sold a girl for wine, that they may drink. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JOL 3:4"},"“Yes, and what are you to me, Tyre, and Sidon, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all the regions of Philistia? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Will you repay me? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["And if you repay me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will swiftly and speedily return your repayment on your own head.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JOL 3:5"},"Because you have taken my silver and my gold, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have carried my finest treasures into your temples, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JOL 3:6"},"and have sold the children of Judah and the children of Jerusalem to the sons of the Greeks,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you may remove them far from their border. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JOL 3:7"},"Behold, I will stir them up out of the place where you have sold them,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will return your repayment on your own head; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JOL 3:8"},"and I will sell your sons and your daughters into the hands of the children of Judah,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will sell them to the men of Sheba, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to a faraway nation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the LORD has spoken it.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JOL 3:9"},"Proclaim this amongst the nations: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Prepare for war! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Stir up the mighty men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let all the warriors draw near. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let them come up. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JOL 3:10"},"Beat your ploughshares into swords, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your pruning hooks into spears. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let the weak say, ‘I am strong.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JOL 3:11"},"Hurry and come, all you surrounding nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and gather yourselves together.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Cause your mighty ones to come down there, LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JOL 3:12"},"“Let the nations arouse themselves, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and come up to the valley of Jehoshaphat; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for there I will sit to judge all the surrounding nations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JOL 3:13"},"Put in the sickle; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the harvest is ripe. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Come, tread, for the wine press is full, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the vats overflow, for their wickedness is great.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JOL 3:14"},"Multitudes, multitudes in the valley of decision! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For the day of the LORD is near, in the valley of decision. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JOL 3:15"},"The sun and the moon are darkened, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the stars withdraw their shining. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JOL 3:16"},"The LORD will roar from Zion, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and thunder from Jerusalem; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the heavens and the earth will shake; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but the LORD will be a refuge to his people, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a stronghold to the children of Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JOL 3:17"},"“So you will know that I am the LORD, your Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["dwelling in Zion, my holy mountain. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Then Jerusalem will be holy, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and no strangers will pass through her any more. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JOL 3:18"},"It will happen in that day, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that the mountains will drop down sweet wine, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the hills will flow with milk, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all the brooks of Judah will flow with waters, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a fountain will flow out from the LORD’s house, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will water the valley of Shittim. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JOL 3:19"},"Egypt will be a desolation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Edom will be a desolate wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the violence done to the children of Judah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because they have shed innocent blood in their land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JOL 3:20"},"But Judah will be inhabited forever, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Jerusalem from generation to generation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JOL 3:21"},"I will cleanse their blood, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that I have not cleansed: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the LORD dwells in Zion.” "]}]}